{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/Learning & Building/Coding/Web Apps/JAMStack/ReactJS/README/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Creating A New React App</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><code>npx create-react-app [app-name]</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Resources</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://reactjsexample.com/\">React.js Examples</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Components</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jerrytigerxu/Notes/blob/master/Learning%20%26%20Building/Coding/Web%20Apps/JAMStack/ReactJS/Fundamentals.md\">How does ReactJS work?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jerrytigerxu/Notes/blob/master/Learning%20%26%20Building/Coding/Web%20Apps/JAMStack/ReactJS/Tips.md\">Tips for working with ReactJS</a></li>\n<li>\n<p>Cheatsheets</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jerrytigerxu/Notes/blob/master/Learning%20%26%20Building/Coding/Web%20Apps/JAMStack/ReactJS/Learn%20ReactJS_%20Part%20I_%20JSX%20Reference%20Guide%20_%20Codecademy.pdf\">JSX</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jerrytigerxu/Notes/blob/master/Learning%20%26%20Building/Coding/Web%20Apps/JAMStack/ReactJS/Learn%20ReactJS_%20Part%20I_%20React%20Components%20Reference%20Guide%20_%20Codecademy.pdf\">Components</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jerrytigerxu/Notes/blob/master/Learning%20%26%20Building/Coding/Web%20Apps/JAMStack/ReactJS/Learn%20ReactJS_%20Part%20I_%20Components%20Interacting%20Reference%20Guide%20_%20Codecademy.pdf\">Component Interaction (<code>props</code> and <code>state</code>)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jerrytigerxu/Notes/blob/master/Learning%20%26%20Building/Coding/Web%20Apps/JAMStack/ReactJS/Learn%20ReactJS_%20Part%20II_%20Stateless%20Components%20From%20Stateful%20Components%20Reference%20Guide%20_%20Codecademy.pdf\">Stateless Components from Stateful Components</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jerrytigerxu/Notes/blob/master/Learning%20%26%20Building/Coding/Web%20Apps/JAMStack/ReactJS/Advanced%20JS.pdf\">Advanced JS</a> </li>\n<li>Styles</li>\n<li>Stateless functional components</li>\n<li>Separating container components from presentational components</li>\n<li>propTypes</li>\n<li>React forms</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jerrytigerxu/Notes/blob/master/Learning%20%26%20Building/Coding/Web%20Apps/JAMStack/ReactJS/lifecycle_methods.jpg\">Lifecycle Methods</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><code>props</code> and <code>state</code></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><code>props</code> should be used to store information that can be changed only by a different component</li>\n<li><code>state</code> should be used to store information that the component itself can change</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":""}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/Learning & Building/Coding/Web Apps/JAMStack/ReactJS/README/"}}}